CONCLUSIONS:
- The accuracy of velocity with th is better than with bf;
- The accuracy of pressure with th is better than with bf, excepted at the first step of time;
- The methods f1 and f2 give the same results;
- The penalization method f1cr by Integral Epsilon P1 P1 dX and
      f1cr Grad Integral Epsilon Grad P1 Grad P1 dX give the same results;
- The penalization method f1cr with Epsilon=1e-7 or 1e-9 give the same results;
- The bf velocity error is divided by 2 when the number of edges is divided by 2;
- The bf pressure max error is divided by more than 5 when the number of edges is divided by 2;
- The th velocity error is divided by 3 when the number of edges is divided by 2;
- The th pressure max error is divided by 3 when the number of edges is divided by 2;
- The CPU time of th is lower than bf with the same mesh;
- The memory storage with f2 is lower than f1;
- The lowest memory storage is obtained with f2cg;

Finally, th f2cg is the best method.
